                        "content": "The nursing instructor asks a nursing student which substance provides a protective function for the stomach against autodigestion and subsequent gastritis. The nursing student responds correctly by identifying which substance?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nGastritis refers to inflammation of the gastric mucosa. Mucosal injury occurs when there is a break in the protective barrier in the stomach lining. Prostaglandins are responsible for the protective mucosal barrier of the stomach lining. Eliminate option 1, as pepsin is a digestive enzyme in the stomach responsible for protein digestion. Eliminate option 2, as gastrin is a hormone that stimulates gastric acid secretion. Eliminate option 3, as ghrelin is a hormone that stimulates appetite. Therefore, since prostaglandins have a role in maintaining the protective stomach lining, option 4 is correct.",
