                        "content": "A client with gastritis experiencing chronic gastric hypersecretion is scheduled for surgery. The nurse teaches the client that the procedure will lessen the stomach's production of acid by altering which structure?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nVagotomy is a procedure that can reduce innervation to the stomach, thereby reducing the production of gastric acid. The portal vein drains venous blood from the stomach. The celiac artery brings arterial blood to the stomach. The pyloric valve separates the stomach from the duodenum. The pyloric valve may undergo surgical repair if it becomes stenosed; this procedure is known as pyloroplasty.",
                        "id": "3ce4c2f5bae34f6f86a2a43b8ac9aaac",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "ef7c4244d2bd44ce9d44a852914a714e",
                                "content": "Monitor strict intake and output"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e220328168914909bebec34abfe47e38",
                                "content": "Administer IV ciprofloxacin as ordered"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "cce4e016259d494da3599fe21e2f183e",
                                "content": "Administer 2 mg oral loperamide as needed every 6 hours for diarrhea"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "6d279730af0447ec9916c154bd01ac97",
                                "content": "Administer intravenous (IV) 0.9% normal saline at 75 milliliters per hour (mL/hr)"
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
