                        "content": "The nurse caring for a client with chronic gastritis understands that the client is at risk for malnutrition. The client is at increased risk for malabsorption if which nutrient is deficient due to the lack of intrinsic factor (IF)?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "c2472dbaf30269ec1d4a4af474a31869",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Understanding 理解",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nChronic gastritis is a diffuse inflammation of the gastric mucosa that results in progressive thinning and atrophy of the stomach lining. As atrophy progresses, the parietal cells become less efficient in secreting intrinsic factor (IF), a substance necessary for vitamin B12 absorption. Inadequate levels of this vitamin result in pernicious anemia. Therefore, option 2 is correct.",
                        "id": "ebc64f3051fe4db0b98ea2312375233a",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
